                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.51/880: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative on Special Mission in Cuba</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crowder</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-08T17:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 8, 1922—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:52 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>75. Because of illness, not serious, which has confined President Zayas to his
                    room since Friday last he has been unable to meet either Governor Harding or the
                    representatives of Morgan and Company. Until conferences have been had am unable
                    to report to the Department terms and conditions on which the loan will be
                    offered to the public.</p>
                <p>Official count recent elections progressing slowly but first indications that
                    Liberals had carried all the provinces except Pinar del Bio are being confirmed
                    as the canvass progresses.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crowder</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
